output2

public void output2()
已过时。 As of JDK version 1.1, replaced by -(Calendar.get(Calendar.ZONE_OFFSET) + Calendar.get(Calendar.DST_OFFSET)) / (60 * 1000). This is add by myself 随意添加 where:
  • d is the day of the month (1 through 31), as one or two decimal digits.
  • mon is the month (Jan, Feb, Mar, Apr, May, Jun, Jul, Aug, Sep, Oct, Nov, Dec).
  • yyyy is the year, as four decimal digits.
  • hh is the hour of the day (00 through 23), as two decimal digits.
  • GMT is exactly the ASCII letters "GMT" to indicate Greenwich Mean Time.

replaced by Calendar.set(Calendar.DAY_OF_MONTH, int date).

随意添加 Returns the offset, measured in minutes, for the local time zone relative to UTC that is appropriate for the time represented by this Date object. 
 new Date(96, 1, 14).getTimezoneOffset() returns 300
because on June 1, 1996, daylight saving time (Eastern Daylight Time) is in use, which is offset only four hours from UTC.

This method produces the same result as if it computed: 

 (this.getTime() - UTC(this.getYear(), 
                       this.getMonth(), 
                       this.getDate(),
                       this.getHours(), 
                       this.getMinutes(), 
                       this.getSeconds())) / (60 * 1000)
